subSubSection.paragraph:
Caterpillars are found in the web of leaves or young shoots twisted together. Young caterpillars feed on buds, then they move on to the leaves (
BRADLEY et al. 1979
). They pupate in a leaf roll along the main vein of the leaf (
KUZNETSOV 1994
) or sometimes on the ground amongst leaf litter in June (
BRADLEY et al. 1979
).
